-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=
  ---| USER MANUAL (v1.4) |---
-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=

--- 1. /register
Command: /register <password> <password> [captcha]
Description: Registers a new account.
Note: If Captcha is enabled, a code will appear in the chat which must be entered as the 3rd argument.

--- 2. /login
Command: /login <password>
Description: Logs the player into their account.

--- 3. /changepass
Command: /changepass <old password> <new password> <new password>
Description: Allows a logged-in player to change their password.

--- 4. /pureauth
Command: /pureauth
Description: [ADMINS ONLY] Displays the help menu with a list of available administrative commands.

--- 5. /pureauth reload
Command: /pureauth reload
Description: Reloads the plugin configuration (messages, settings, and language) without restarting the server.

--- 6. /pureauth unregister
Command: /pureauth unregister <player>
Description: Deletes a player's account from the database.
(Subject to SAFE-MODE restrictions).

--- 7. /pureauth register
Command: /pureauth register <player> <password>
Description: [ADMIN] Manually registers an account for a player (online or offline).
(Subject to SAFE-MODE restrictions).

--- 8. /pureauth forcelogin
Command: /pureauth forcelogin <player>
Description: Forcefully logs in a specific player (bypassing the password requirement).
(Subject to SAFE-MODE restrictions).

--- 9. /pureauth location
Command: /pureauth location <login|register>
Description: Sets the global teleport location for authentication.

'login': Where players are teleported when they join and need to log in.

'register': Where unregistered players are teleported.
(Note: Set this at your current physical position).

--- 10. /pureauth info
Command: /pureauth info <player>
Description: Displays detailed information about a player: Registration IP, Last Login IP, and Last Login Timestamp.

--- 11. /pureauth setpassword
Command: /pureauth setpassword <player> <new password>
Description: Administratively changes a player's password (does not require the old password).
(Subject to SAFE-MODE restrictions).

--- 12. /pureauth accounts
Command: /pureauth accounts <IP>
Description: Lists all usernames registered to a specific IP address.

--- 13. /pureauth stats
Command: /pureauth stats
Description: [CONSOLE ONLY] Displays a comprehensive report of the plugin status, including total users, database connection, and EVERY configuration setting (Safe Mode status, Captcha settings, Timeouts, etc.).

--- Configuration & System Notes ---

To change messages, colors, login duration, max attempts, session time, and IP limits â€“ see the config.yml configuration file.

New Features in v1.4:

Language Support: Switch between EN (English) and PL (Polish) in config.yml.

Captcha System: Adds a required verification code during registration (can be disabled).

Safe Mode: If enabled, sensitive admin commands (register, unregister, forcelogin, setpassword) are blocked in-game and only work from the Console.

Blindness Toggle: Option to enable/disable the blindness effect during login.

Fail-Safe: The plugin automatically blocks connections if online-mode=true is detected in server.properties.

The plugin is for Minecraft version 1.21.X.
The plugin was programmed with the Paper engine in mind.
The plugin was written using JDK-21.
